CCN-DNS Project Development Log & Technology Stack
===================================================

This log documents the tools, languages, and architecture components used to build the complete DNS Resolution Service.

1. Architecture
----------------
- C++ Engine (Backend resolver): Parses standard DNS UDP/TCP packets, implements LRU caching, traverses delegation hierarchies, manages socket timeouts.
- Python Flask REST API (Middleware): Interfaces with the C++ executable via subprocess wrappers and stdout parsing. Features a second latency-optimized cache, connection metrics, benchmarking logic, rate tracking.
- Browser Frontend (Web Dashboard): Serves an interactive HTML dashboard using pure Vanilla JS/CSS for minimal overhead.

2. Languages
-------------
- C++ (Standard: C++17) for the core networking and packet manipulation.
- Python 3 for the API layer and background processing.
- HTML5 / CSS3 / Vanilla JavaScript (ES6) for the user interface.

3. Core Libraries & APIs
-------------------------
C++ Standard Library:
- <winsock2.h> / <sys/socket.h>: Low-level UDP and TCP network sockets.
- <chrono>: Precision timeout implementations.
- <random>: Transaction ID and root-server selection randomization.
- <mutex> / <list> / <map>: Real-time thread-safe LRU caching.

Python:
- Flask (v2.3.0+): Main REST API framework.
- Flask-CORS (v4.0.0+): For allowing Cross-Origin resource sharing directly to the dashboard.
- Requests: Used strictly during the integration test suite (`pytest`) to hit API endpoints.
- struct / socket: Used in Python middleware to execute low-level UDP queries to Google (8.8.8.8) and Cloudflare (1.1.1.1) for dashboard benchmarking comparisons.
- subprocess: Sandboxed bridging to the C++ executable.

4. UI Design System
--------------------
- Styling: Dark mode glassmorphism UI. Custom pure-CSS styles without bulk frameworks (No Tailwind).
- Fonts: Google Fonts (Inter, JetBrains Mono).
- Components: Grid metrics panel, auto-updating table displays, resolution path viz, recursive node graphics.

5. Utilities
-------------
- MSYS2 / MinGW-w64 (g++): The compiler toolchain used for C++ on Windows.
- Pytest: For comprehensive system testing.
- Git: Source control.

6. Standards 
-------------
- RFC 1035: Domain Names - Implementation and Specification (Framing, Compression, Delegation).
- RFC 1034: Domain Names - Concepts and Facilities.
